The evidence with the title 'Gun homicide rate down 49% since 1993 peak; public unaware ... ' says May 7, 2013  ... Gun homicide rate down 49 % since 1993 peak; public unaware. Pace of decline slows in past decade . By D'Vera Cohn,  ... It was two decades ago . According to a new Pew Research Center survey , today 56% of Americans believe gun crime is higher than 20 years ago and only 12 % think it is lower. 
